properties.areaDesc: North Mobile Bay; Western Choctawhatchee Bay; Perdido Bay Area; Pensacola Bay Area including Santa Rosa Sound; Eastern Choctawhatchee Bay
properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued February 5 at 4:35AM CST until February 5 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Mobile AL
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Dense Fog Advisory, dense fog will reduce
visibility to 1 nautical mile or less. For the Small Craft
Advisory, south to southwest winds up to 20 knots tonight and
Thursday morning, becoming west to northwest winds 15 to 25
knots with gusts up to 30 knots Thursday afternoon into Thursday
night. Waves up to 3 feet in the bays and sounds.

* WHERE...Northern Mobile Bay, Perdido Bay, Pensacola Bay
System, Western Choctawhatchee Bay and Eastern Choctawhatchee
Bay.

* WHEN...For the Dense Fog Advisory, until noon CST today. For
the Small Craft Advisory, from 6 PM this evening to 6 AM CST
Friday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft. Low
visibility will make navigation difficult.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating smaller
vessels, should avoid navigating in hazardous conditions.

If you must navigate, proceed with caution. Use proper fog
signals. Make sure all running lights are on. Remember to use
your radar and compass.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON CST TODAY... ...SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO 6 AM CST FRIDAY
